// safeT PTT iOS — per-machine configuration template (OPTIONAL).
//
// You do NOT need to edit anything here to talk to production. The app already
// defaults to the production server:
//
//     APIBaseURL = https://safet-ptt.com   (hard-set in project.yml → Info.plist)
//
// `./setup.sh` copies this file to `Local.xcconfig` (gitignored) just so Xcode
// always has a config file to attach. Leave it as-is for normal use.
//
// Only change SAFET_API_BASE_URL below if you are pointing the app at a
// DIFFERENT server (e.g. a local dev box) AND you wire it into the target's
// APIBaseURL Info.plist key in project.yml.
//
// Auth is per-user: sign in with your username + password on the login screen
// and the server's JWT is used for every request.
//
// NOTE: xcconfig treats `//` as a start-of-line-comment, so URL values must
// split the protocol's `//` with `$()` — an empty variable expansion that
// defeats the comment parser. Keep that pattern when editing.

SAFET_API_BASE_URL = https:$()//safet-ptt.com
